<item>
            <title>[LU-329] ost_lock_get() is not put in some cases</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-329</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;While adapting &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-234&quot; title=&quot;OOM killer causes node hang&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-234&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-234&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; to our branch I&apos;ve found that ost_lock_put() is not called in some error cases. &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-234&quot; title=&quot;OOM killer causes node hang&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-234&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-234&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; added even more such cases. Please check patch attached. I have the question there - do we need to report repbody in case of error in ost_punch()? I doubt that but it is always returned there no matter is &apos;rc&apos; zero or not.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="10879">LU-329</key>
